com.preemptive.instrumentation

Class Log4JAppender

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.log4j.AppenderSkeleton
      • com.preemptive.instrumentation.Log4JAppender
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Appender, OptionHandler

    public class Log4JAppender
extends AppenderSkeleton
    This log4j appender sends messages to the PreEmptive Analytics server.

    The appender use the following parameters:

    • applicationId - GUID of the the application. Required if the application does not start PA itself. See RuntimeIntelligence.setApplicationId(java.lang.String).
    • applicationInstance - an identifier for the instance of the application, typically a serial number. See RuntimeIntelligence.setApplicationInstance(java.lang.String).
    • applicationName - a name for the application. See RuntimeIntelligence.setApplicationName(java.lang.String).
    • applicationType - a string characterizing the type of the application. See RuntimeIntelligence.setApplicationType(java.lang.String).
    • applicationVersion - a version string for the application. See RuntimeIntelligence.setApplicationVersion(java.lang.String).
    • companyId - GUID for the company providing the application. Required if the application does not start PA itself. See RuntimeIntelligence.setCompanyId(java.lang.String).
    • companyName - a name for the company. See RuntimeIntelligence.setCompanyName(java.lang.String).
    • endpoint - the endpoint of the PA server. Defaults to commercial PA endpoint. See RuntimeIntelligence.setServiceEndpoint(java.lang.String).
    • useSsl - boolean, should SSL be used to send messages to the endpoint. Defaults to true . See RuntimeIntelligence.setUseSsl(boolean).
    • fullDataMode - boolean, should PA gather full data when possible. Defaults to false. See RuntimeIntelligence.setFullDataMode(boolean).
    • sendDisabled - boolean, should PA not send data to the server. Defaults to false (sends data). See RuntimeIntelligence.setSendDisabled(boolean).
    • supportOfflineMode - boolean, should messages not sent to the server be stored locally. Defaults to false (discard messages). See RuntimeIntelligence.setSupportOfflineMode(boolean).
    • sendInterval - integer, milliseconds between sending messages to the server. See RuntimeIntelligence.setSendInterval(int).
    • flowController - the name of a class that implements FlowController. See RuntimeIntelligence.setFlowController(com.preemptive.instrumentation.FlowController)
    • binaryName - a name to be associated for a module (jar, package, etc).
    • binaryId - GUID for the executable a module (jar, package, etc).
    • binaryVersion - a version for a module (jar, package, etc).
    • nameLayout - A layout string used to create the PA feature name for logging events. Defaults to %c.%p. If set to an empty string then feature messages are not generated.
    • propertiesLayout - A layout string used to create the properties that accompany PA feature and fault messages. This is used to format the input for Properties.load(java.io.Reader). Properties are placed on individual lines and are separated using %n. The default value is message=%m.
    • systemProfile - boolean, generate an PA system profile message on start up. See RuntimeIntelligence.systemProfile()
    All parameters are optional unless otherwise specified.

    Binary information (binaryName, binaryId, binaryVersion) are used when multiple appender instances are associated with different packages or jars.

    Note: if the PreEmptive Analytics system has been configured and started by the application or by another Appender then the configuration parameters will be ignored.
